# Ghost_Monkey Project Structure

This is an educational UNIX backdoor written in Nim for authorized penetration testing and OSCP preparation.

## Core Components

- [client.nim](mdc:client.nim) - Interactive socket client that connects to the implant
- [implant.nim](mdc:implant.nim) - Socket server that executes commands via `execProcess()`
- [config.nims](mdc:config.nims) - Nim compiler configuration
- [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) - Comprehensive development and safety guidelines

## Architecture

Simple client-server backdoor pattern using TCP sockets:

1. Client connects to implant on port 5555
2. Commands sent via unauthenticated TCP protocol
3. Implant executes commands using `execProcess()` and returns output
4. Both components use the `strenc` module
